<paragraph pageId="23" pageNumber="72">
The type specimen was distributed as 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Compositae" genus="Vernonia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Vernonia triflora" order="Asterales" pageId="23" pageNumber="72" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="triflora">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="72">Vernonia triflora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Brem., which differs by having only 3 florets in its capitula, stiffly and densely hispid stems, and ovate to oblong leaf blades with hispidulous abaxial surfaces.
</paragraph>
